    <string name="terms_of_use_text"><b>hibts Global Terms of Use &amp; Privacy Policy (GDPR &amp; International Standards)</b>\n\n1. <b>Acceptance:</b> By using hibts, you agree to these terms. hibts is designed to help you track habits and tasks personally.\n\n2. <b>Data Privacy (GDPR):</b> Your privacy is our priority. For users in the EU and globally, all habit and task data is stored <b>locally on your device</b> by default. We do not have access to your private lists unless you manually perform a backup.\n\n3. <b>Data Ownership:</b> You own 100% of your data. You can export it using the Backup feature or delete it permanently using \"Delete All App Data\".\n\n4. <b>User Eligibility:</b> The app is suitable for users aged 13 and above (16+ in EU/EEA under GDPR).\n\n5. <b>No Medical Advice:</b> hibts is a productivity tool. It does not provide medical, mental health, or fitness advice. Consult a professional for such needs.\n\n6. <b>Limitation of Liability:</b> We strive for 100% stability, but we are not liable for data loss due to device failure or accidental deletion. Please use the Backup feature regularly.\n\n7. <b>Termination:</b> You may stop using the service at any time by deleting the app. Deleting the app also deletes local data.</string>
